A consultant since 1988, Stewart conducts pre-investment due diligence and researches new business and venture opportunities for private investors, venture capital firms and R&amp;D funding agencies. He has a particular focus on agriculture, biotechnology, environmental services and applied science and technology. <br /><br />Stewart has a Ph.D. in Physical Organic Chemistry from the University of Alberta and an MBA in Entrepreneurship and Venture Development from the University of Calgary. He has conducted business throughout North America, Europe, Africa and Asia-Pacific.<br />